      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 9
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2006 Mitsubishi Lancer Evolution IX MR represents the pinnacle of the CT9A platform. Under the hood, the legendary 4G63 MIVEC engine delivers linear boost through its factory twin-scroll turbocharger, paired with a crisp 6-speed close-ratio manual transmission. The sophisticated drivetrain features a fully functional Active Center Differential (ACD) with three selectable modes, ensuring precise torque distribution. The chassis is supported by Bilstein monotube dampers and Brembo four-piston calipers, offering exceptional damping and thermal capacity. While displaying the honest patina of a driven car, the mechanicals remain tight, with the helical front LSD providing superb traction out of the apex. A well-sorted example for the driver who prioritizes raw chassis feedback and 4G63 performance.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.8,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 9
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_3",
      "description": "Used car in good condition. Reliable engine. Clean interior. Minor exterior wear. Service history included. No issues.",
      "price": 32000.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 9
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_4_listing_4",
      "firm_id": "sybil_4",
      "description": "This vehicle is a wonderful example of pride of ownership, offering a reliable and premium driving experience. The exterior paint retains a high-gloss finish, though upon close inspection, you will find minor road-rash stone chips on the front fascia and a small, professionally touched-up scratch on the passenger door\u2014typical for a car that has been driven responsibly. The alloy wheels are in great shape with only very light curb rash on the rear right wheel. Inside, the cabin is pristine and strictly non-smoker; the leather seats show light natural creasing but no tears or thinning. All interior electronics, including the premium audio system, navigation, and heated seats, are fully operational. Mechanically, the car is robust. It has been serviced every 5,000 miles with full synthetic oil, and the most recent inspection confirms that the suspension is tight and the engine runs smoothly without any leaks or unusual noises. The tires are matching all-seasons with plenty of tread depth left for several seasons, and the brakes provide firm, confident stopping power. This car drives straight and true, providing a quiet, comfortable ride that feels much newer than its mileage suggests. It comes complete with two key fobs, the original owner's manual, and a documented service history.",
      "price": 33800.0,
      "reputation": 0.3,
